Task
Number in four different number systems
Write a function named convertNumber that takes a positive decimal integer num as an argument and returns an array in decimal, binary, octal, and hexadecimal notation.
Examples:
• the convertNumber (5) function should return [5, 101, 5, 5];
• function convertNumber (9) should return [9, 1001, 11, 9];
• the convertNumber (12) function should return [12, 1100, 14, "c"];
• the convertNumber (32) function should return [32, 100000, 40, "20"].

Solution
function convertNumber (num) {
 return [num, + num.toString (2), + num.toString (8), num.toString (16)];
}
